i5.las2peer.p2p

Class PastryNodeImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • i5.las2peer.p2p.Node
      • i5.las2peer.p2p.PastryNodeImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    L2pStorageInterface, NodeStorageInterface, AgentStorage

    public class PastryNodeImpl
extends Node
    A FreePastry implementation of a las2peer Node. This class is the actual heart of the p2p based network of interacting nodes an agents in the las2peer setting. The package i5.las2peer.p2p.pastry provides all necessary helper classes for the integration (and encapsulation) of the FreePastry library.

    • Constructor Detail

      • PastryNodeImpl

        public PastryNodeImpl(L2pClassManager classLoader,
                      boolean useMonitoringObserver,
                      int port,
                      java.lang.String bootstrap,
                      SharedStorage.STORAGE_MODE storageMode,
                      java.lang.Long nodeIdSeed)
        This is the regular constructor used by the L2pNodeLauncher. Its parameters can be set to start a new network or join an existing Pastry ring.
        Parameters:
        classLoader - A class loader that is used by the node.
        useMonitoringObserver - If true, the node sends monitoring information to the monitoring service.
        port - A port number the PastryNode should listen to for network communication.
        bootstrap - A bootstrap address that should be used, like hostname:port or null to start a new network.
        storageMode - A storage mode to be used by this node, see SharedStorage.STORAGE_MODE.
        nodeIdSeed - A node id (random) seed to enforce a specific node id. If null, the node id will be random.

      • PastryNodeImpl

        public PastryNodeImpl(java.lang.String bootstrap,
                      SharedStorage.STORAGE_MODE storageMode,
                      java.lang.String storageDir,
                      java.lang.Long nodeIdSeed)
        This constructor is mainly used by the TestSuite and sets all parameters for debugging and testing operation mode.
        Parameters:
        bootstrap - A bootstrap address that should be used, like hostname:port or null to start a new network.
        storageMode - A storage mode to be used by this node, see SharedStorage.STORAGE_MODE.
        storageDir - A directory to persist data to. Only considered in persistent storage mode, but overwrites SharedStorage configurations.
        nodeIdSeed - A node id (random) seed to enforce a specific node id. If null, the node id will be random.
